GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF NORTH CAROLINA
SESSION 2025
S 1
SENATE BILL 585
Short Title: Local Govts/Mental Health/ CC Tuition Waiver. (Public)
Sponsors: Senator Murdock (Primary Sponsor).
Referred to: Rules and Operations of the Senate
March 26, 2025
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT PROVIDING THAT CERTAIN MENTAL HEALTH CLINICIANS AND PEER
3 SUPPORT SPECIALISTS IN MUNICIPAL AND COUNTY EMS OR RESCUE AND
4 LIFESAVING DEPARTMENTS MAY RECEIVE A WAIVER OF TUITION AND
5 REGISTRATION FEES WHEN ATTENDING COMMUNITY COLLEGE.
6 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
7 SECTION 1. G.S. 115D-5 reads as rewritten:
8 "§ 115D-5. Administration of institutions by State Board of Community Colleges;
9 personnel exempt from North Carolina Human Resources Act; extension
10 courses; tuition waiver; in-plant training; contracting, etc., for establishment
11 and operation of extension units of the community college system; use of existing
12 public school facilities.
13 …
14 (b) In order to make instruction as accessible as possible to all citizens, the teaching of
15 curricular courses and of noncurricular extension courses at convenient locations away from
16 institution campuses as well as on campuses is authorized and shall be encouraged. A pro rata
17 portion of the established regular tuition rate charged a full-time student shall be charged a
18 part-time student taking any curriculum course. In lieu of any tuition charge, the State Board of
19 Community Colleges shall establish a uniform registration fee, or a schedule of uniform
20 registration fees, to be charged students enrolling in extension courses for which instruction is
21 financed primarily from State funds. The State Board of Community Colleges may provide by
22 general and uniform regulations for waiver of tuition and registration fees for the following:
23 …
24 (2) Courses requested by the following entities that support the organizations'
25 training needs and are on a specialized course list approved by the State Board
26 of Community Colleges:
27 …
28 d. Municipal, county, or State EMS or rescue and lifesaving departments.
29 This sub-subdivision includes municipal and county departments
30 whose primary responsibility is to (i) embed mental health clinicians
31 in 911 call centers to assist in directing and providing appropriate
32 resources to calls for service and (ii) pair mental health clinicians, peer
33 support specialists, and other trained professionals with first
34 responders to respond to calls for service.
35 …."
36 SECTION 2. This act becomes effective July 1, 2025.
*S585-v-1*

